item.description:
Last week we were fortunate to have Daniel Galhardo, owner of Tenkara USA visit our office and he had a few minutes to stop by for a podcast interview.&nbsp; In this week&rsquo;s discussion, he talks about what he has learned since his original podcast with us, especially about fly patterns and the rationale for using a single fly.&nbsp; He also talks about&mdash;gasp&mdash;fishing a huge streamer from Shawn Combs&rsquo; drift boat with his Tenkara rod.&nbsp; So much for being a purist.
&nbsp;
Even if you are not interested in Tenkara fishing you will probably find something of interest in this week&rsquo;s podcast.&nbsp; We tackle questions about rinsing gear after saltwater use, how much backing to put on a reel with a sinking line, the use of stinger hooks on saltwater flies, fishing lake-run browns and steelhead in the Great Lakes in estuaries, whether metal studs spook trout, and a great tip from a listener for cleaning your fly tying bench.

